"{\"paper\": {\"status\": \"map_review\", \"title\": \"A Classification Algorithm for Predicting the Structure of Summaries\", \"url\": \"http://www.aclweb.org/anthology/W09-2807\", \"abstract\": \"We investigate the problem of generating the structure of short domain independent abstracts. We apply a supervised machine learning approach trained over a set of abstracts collected from abstracting services and automatically annotated with a text analysis tool. We design a set of features for learning inspired from past research in content selection, information ordering, and rhetorical analysis for training an algorithm which then predicts the discourse structure of unseen abstracts. The proposed approach to the problem which combines local and contextual features is able to predict the local structure of the abstracts in just over 60% of the cases.\", \"field\": \"summarization; abstract generation; discourse structure\", \"user\": \"surveyor\"}, \"map_name\": \"A_Classification_Alg_0.html\", \"_id\": {\"$oid\": \"596bc9259e48ca2bd80590c1\"}, \"annotation\": {\"metrics\": [{\"type\": \"Quantitative\", \"name\": \"predict discourse structure_Average accuracy\", \"task_name\": {\"name\": \"predict discourse structure\"}, \"measure\": \"Average accuracy\"}], \"tasks\": [{\"name\": \"predict discourse structure\"}, {\"name\": \"Predicate-based Generation\"}, {\"name\": \"Position-based Generation\"}, {\"name\": \"tf*idf-based Generation\"}, {\"name\": \"Summarization-based Generation\"}, {\"name\": \"abstract generation\"}, {\"name\": \"local features\"}, {\"name\": \"contextual features\"}, {\"name\": \"supervised machine learning\"}], \"datasets\": [{\"comment\": \"contain predicates which appeared at least 5 times in the corpus.  With this restriction  in  place  the  original  set  of  predicates used to create the discourse structure is reduced to sixteen\", \"field\": \"LISA,  ERIC,  and  Internet &  Personal  Computing  Abstracts\", \"name\": \"Saggion 2009\", \"l